node.text: Really starting to understand deck life.
You will never get the crumbs of this moose leg from my mouth!
Waiting for the weekend!
Big park plays = big snoozes
Get out of bed!
And for those of you wondering, this is the sign on the gate. Some humans are just not very smart...
Sometimes people leave the gate open, that’s my chance to escape!
Can we go home yet?
Diggers.
What no dog policy?
Construction dog approves this structure.
Good morning everyone.
When life gives you lemons, use them to disappoint and confuse your beagle!
Elvis when his best friend leaves the room.
Why did Andrew destroy the backyard? It was perfectly fine, a little poop covered, but perfectly fine otherwise.
Waiting for coffee at @roostercoffee
Smile for the camera Elvis!
Where is Elvis?
Today i made a friend, Nori the Euraser @jenrqz @dankalmar
You Bath me, i sit on your clean laundry. Fair deal?
I don’t care what you think i did to your sock!
ZzzZzzzzz
Feeling wiggly
After a big off leash play at Bellwoods I’m home alone, Andrew is off to New York. I hope Amanda feeds me...
So many Pugs in the park!
Today i was allowed off leash at the beach. Everything went well, i didn’t run away even once. To celebrate we did a photo shoot where i stuck out my tongue.
Feeling snoozy. Glad the weekend is here!
Reflecting on the fact that someone stole my Nylabones 👮🏽‍♂️👮‍♀️Seriously...they broke into the office and stole them along with other, unimportant (to a dog), things.
Some product placement to start the morning. In all seriousness, he stole the empty container out of the trash, i kind of felt like he deserved to keep it?
This one?
Just a little in the way...
I’m a bad dog
Yesterday we had a small party with lots of dog friends to celebrate Elvis. Unfortunately @pinotinthecity got some cake on her face, but hopefully we can still be friends...

Fetch in its traditional sense doesn’t work with Elvis, he likes to play tug-of-war when i ask for the ball back. So instead we play “trade” where i get him to drop one ball in return for me throwing another. It works shockingly well!
Caught snoozing with the moose

Apparently it’s #nationalpetday? Elvis is a rescue dog, and these pictures are from the first time we met up until recently. He had a big limp due to his last surgery not going well, and the first 3 months of us knowing each other were mostly about getting him walking again. The first thing he did when we met was come up to the glass at his kennel and lay on my fingers when i stuck them under the door. Now he is basically my shadow wherever i go.
Human thought i was smelly, so he wet me...now I’m grumpy
Got this jumping business figured out, part horse for sure.
Mmmmm moose.
Car ride naps
The Beagle has landed!
Still trying...
Still learning...
Zzzz...
After spending an entire day in bed because the humans were sick, they spring on me that i have to go to work today?!

On March 29th I was officially adopted. It took so long because the great people at @toronto_humane_society wanted to be sure my leg was good before they let me go. It was a big day for me, so my friend @christinanicoleg insisted i dress up for the occasion. There will be a party, expect invites! (This isn’t an April fools day joke!)
Late night walks.
@birdfacee got me a, tight, Canada day outfit.
This is a good start to the long weekend.
When the humans go out they watch me...or maybe it’s the aliens!  I watch back so they know, i know. The truth is out there.
If they don’t want me to stand on the table, they should leave my bones on the floor
The weekly iteration meeting always takes it out of me...
If no one is pulling back, this ball isn’t interesting, but as soon as someone plays along...it’s on!
This is why @andrewjmcgrath has no finger tips to his gloves these days.
Elvis isn’t a fan of #earthhour #soundon🔊
Good news guys, my leg doesn’t seem to hurt today! Back to building muscle soon...

For #nationalpuppyday i decided to hurt my leg again (but it didn’t stop me wagging my tail!), so @andrewjmcgrath took me home to rest and I’ve started feeling better again. Recovery is a long and slow road it seems!
This was me last Saturday at @fourpawsrehabtoronto. They really got me back on my feet, now i need to build muscle to finish the job! 💥💥💥💪💪💪
I beagled a little too hard today and my nose lead me under the steps. Now I’m stuck, just great...
With my wonky leg i cannot climb towers, so I’m raising money my own way, by eating!
Fav spot, in the sun, by the door. Perfect.
Woodland adventures!
Just found the dog sitting, paws crossed. Not staged. He has life figured out at a level i can not comprehend.
Working hard or hardly working?
Paw and pow!
Guys, checkout how square my sits are! And yes, i know i have food on my nose...
I’m not allowed to sit on these blankets, and i know it...which is why I’m looking so guilty.
When i focus rrreeeaaalllyyy hard i have to stick my tongue out to help solve the problem.
Good morning
Slow down, take it easy...they keep telling me these things, but i just don’t want to hear it.
Comfortable? Maybe...
Reunited
I reeeeally didn’t want to get out of bed today. Since when is 6.30 a thing?!
Yesterday i went for a walk in the park during rehab. Today I’m at the vet getting my leg checked out, hopefully they’re happy with my progress!
Guys, it turns out I’m all Beagle! Who knew...you can see all my DNA test results here http://EMBK.ME/ELVIS8
I’m terrifying...
Monday, I’d rather be in bed.
Cries to go out, cries to come in. Repeat.
Must, eat, hat...
Andrew is home sick again, my leg is sore...but it’s not all bad i suppose.
Tired. When i pull this face I’m told i look like an alligator.
Sure am lucky I’m cute. Decided to eat @andrewjmcgrath’s glasses today, he was pretty upset with me. Hope he keeps feeding me, i like food.
@andrewjmcgrath is home with me today, not sure why we didn’t go to the office? Loving this sun.
Leave me alone, sleeping.
You know you’ve made it in life when you see your name written in peanut butter!
Today they made me run super hard in the water, now I’m super exhausted.
This picture: Food going in, or coming out? You decide!
Great party, thanks for the invite @checkout51
Big workout == big snoozes.
This scary ground lives between the office and the parking lot, i really don’t enjoy walking over it.
Went for a walk, got to wear this flashy attachment. Everyone loves it, except me.
I know it creeps @andrewjmcgrath out when i sit here and watch, silently. So i do it all the time.
This guy tried to get my attention with weird noises so i threw a head tilt into the equation. Road trip weekend!
Went on a big walk, suuuuppper sleepy now.
New favour of @acanapetfood. Turns out i eat healthier than the humans.
@andrewjmcgrath made me run, now I’m super sleepy. Brb in 1 hour when I’m all energetic again.
Met a new friend, tried to play but he’s more into snorting than playing.
I really liked the bag @christinanicoleg let me take home for a few days, so @andrewjmcgrath got me my own. Blue is totally my colour!
I get angry at the Amazon people when they drop off packages
💤💤💤 today was a big day
Playing with my pal River.
Packed day at the office. Slept next to my friend @balzner and fought off Paolo who decided to steal my bones :(
Dog has an ice problem...
Naps with friends.
Every day this jerk makes me do some kind of routine just to get my food.
They made me RUN in the water this weekend, sore and tired today, but it was worth it.
Had a bath, now i nap.
Today we found a shoe, and a hill with sticks growing out of the ground, so i ate both the shoe and sticks.

The moment i got away from @andrewjmcgrath, although he managed to grab me again with a very impressive baseball slide for my leash. I want to be trusted off leash, but i cannot help but follow my nose.
So, just like every day, today is leg day for me. My friend @christinanicoleg leant me a swell backpack to carry around some rice and sand, it’s pretty fun to wear and helps me get stronger.
Is it Friday yet? Please let it be Friday.
Today i was forced to file my bones neatly before i left for the day. They were all over the office, it just had to happen.
Throwback to the cone days.
Another morning ritual is running around like crazy for an hour and then getting exhausted, crashing out in someone’s lap.
Waiting for @andrewjmcgrath to finish in the shower, a daily ritual.
I know my instagram makes me look super lazy, that isn’t the case, i run sometimes.
No treats, no paw! #beaglesofinstagram
But why? #beaglesofinstagram
Waiting for the pizza to be ready, get out of my way!
Too lazy to care.
New favourite toy
Practicing self control, even when my nose says do it, i can resist!
So lazy, didn’t want to go for a walk, especially didn’t care for getting dressed up.
Sure it’s cold out (-11C) but there is sun, so I’ll sit here anyway.
Played a lot of office fetch, current status: exhausted
Lazzzy
Car rides are a great place to sleep, but the fresh snow meant it was a little too bright for my liking today.
Today I’m busy helping @andrewjmcgrath upgrade to Ubuntu Xenial64 (whatever that means??)
Zzz...
Please put me down...
Feed me
This ball is amazing, why has it been hiding from me all this time?
This is here for me, right?
So comfortable. @andrewjmcgrath missed by rehab appointment (he’s a stupid guy sometimes...) so I’m just relaxing instead.
I really do find the daily stand-up meeting super boring.
Road trip!
Had a bit of a bark, out of character but it happens.
Please hurry up @andrewjmcgrath, I’m going to be late for a very important meeting.
Nightly “hide my head and snooze” session has begun.
Just walking down the street, like a normal dog...which isn’t super normal for me.
Guys, i found the sun.
This is me, starting around 6pm until 9am.

So it’s been a lot of work, and there is still more to do, but Elvis is really making some astounding progress at getting back on all four legs after his FHO. It’s been 6 weeks since surgery, but thanks to the rehab work done with the @toronto_humane_society (big shout out to @christinanicoleg !!) and @fourpawsrehabtoronto he has, literally, taken some massive steps forward. First video is his first water rehab session, last was his most recent today. Some progress shots in the middle for fun :)
I just got home from @fourpawsrehabtoronto and i felt pretty spunky. But then things changed, so @andrewjmcgrath moved my bed into the sun for me.
Not totally sure how i got here, but now I’m trapped...help?
I found a new spot that i really really like!
We just arrived at work, can you tell I’m excited? @andrewjmcgrath says I’m being dramatic and it’s actually pretty fun.
My chair, go away please. #beaglesofinstagram
Sometimes I’m just too cute (photo credit @rebeccamartin) #beaglesofinstagram
So, someone, got into the donuts...ugh
Just another day at the office. #beaglesofinstagram
Major head tilts for this confusing sound.
Caught sitting on the couch, only allowed here on invitation. I wasn’t invited. #beaglesofinstagram
Just destroyed this carrot, feeling pretty good about it.
After a walk on the water treadmill i got a good pampering. Thanks @fourpawsrehabtoronto
Please stop sitting at that desk and play with me...
Too. Lazy. To. Play... #beagle #beaglesofinstagram
I almost managed to get away with a glove. Almost...
While @andrewjmcgrath was working i snuck on the couch to watch some figure skating and nap. #beaglesofinstagram #postopfho
3rd water rehab session. Today i walked in the water for a whole 14 minutes (twice as long as last time). The treadmill was faster and they even lowered the water level to make it harder (not shown)
Sometimes i start to go upstairs, then forget how to get back down, so i just look at everyone until they help me. #beaglesofinstagram
Why does shower water taste so good?!
Found my sun spot, time for another snooze.
I really wanted to eat this stick, but then i fell asleep with it in my mouth...whoops!
Fireplace is the best place
Too tired for opening presents
Jokes on you guys, i can walk, if i want to.
As a reward for going outside in the snow to pee, @andrewjmcgrath and i played a game! I think he was just trying to make me use my bad leg though...that guy...
I went for a walk, like my jacket?
Today i went for another walk in the water, it’s fun.
Excited for rehab!
I thought i wanted a shower, all i actually needed was a drink.
Helping wrap presents is my favourite activity, i like eating the tape and chewing on scissors
